SUMMARY:Rewind / Rebound
DESCRIPTION:Memory is not a recording. It is a negotiation. \nRewind / Rebound is a trio performance that treats time as something that can be reversed\, reconstructed\, and remade. What is remembered is never quite what happened. What is lost generates something new. \nThe performance unfolds in three phases: expression\, rewind\, and rebound. What begins as improvisation is reconstructed in reverse\, and what cannot be perfectly recalled becomes the material for what comes next. Each mistake becomes choreography. Each return reshapes what came before.  \nThree performers. Three phases. Three histories. \nSupported by: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/rewind-rebound/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Dance,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail-117.jpg
END:VEVENT
